{
  "texts": [
    "Each z i is a combination of the cell state contributions ζ(k, x i) weighted by the proportions c i.",
    "The cell state proportions are inferred with the neural network γ, which is guided toward the prior to match the cell type gene sets.",
    "The prior strength parameter α also premultiplies the neural network γ to obtain a posterior of similar strength, which helps for the gradient optimization.",
    "Next, the standard variational inference that maximizes the evidence lower bound (ELBO) is performed 84.",
    "The ELBO in our case can be written as:, z, l, c, u;α, A, l, σ)"
  ]
}